}




The health expert explains that the cold water could cause a skin condition called flaking, which makes layers of the skin peel off. With most of the residents walking in the affected water without protective shoes such as gumboot, Dr Mwenda cautions that bilharzia is also a risk, in addition to colds and fever, which he says affects small children, confirming what the chemist has noted in the past three weeks.   



