Nasty surprise 

Attempts to get an interview with Nairobi Water were futile, with the questions sent by the Nation to the company remaining unanswered by the time of going to print. 

No government entity is taking responsibility to right the wrong, as the affected residents hope that the government will act speedily to end their perpetual agony. 

Every rainy season, they are displaced by the rain water, but this year’s nasty surprise in the name of the sewage makes the situation especially dire. The cost of running the SGR was the highest in 2019, hitting Sh18bn against the Sh13.5bn in revenues generated for the year. The President and Mr Odinga are expected to launch the nationwide Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) campaigns on Monday. The DP has poked holes in the BBI but has refused to oppose it outright even under pressure from some of his allies.